The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, October 07, 2002  Calcutta Column
				 																																									Parking fees are not uniform across the city. Moreover, most parking lot attendants do not have the documents to show that they have been appointed by the Corporation. Both the Calcutta and Howrah civic bodies should standardise the parking rates and make the attendants wear uniforms.				 																																									B.N. Bose,				 																																									Dum Dum.				 																																									Government vehicles, especially those belonging to the Posts amp; Telegraph department carrying mail and cargo, always flout traffic rules. It is even more ironical because the slogans written on the rear of these vehicles insist commuters and vehicles to follow traffic rules. The government should look into the matter.				 																																									Sumant Poddar,				 																																									Kyd Street.
